1- install docker
2- install docker-compose
3- cp elasticsearch.yml.tml to elasticsearch.yml
4- add elasticsearch config and/or aws secret keys to elasticsearch.yml accordingly
5- to add additionall service instances, uncomment related lines in docker-compose.yml and create esdata* and snapshot* folders accordingly
6- run docker-compose up -d
7- test elastic search running "http :9200"
8- test mongodb running "mongo" client
9- test redis-server running "redis-cli" and then "set key value"

